                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#9v" facs="010">Fol. 9v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#10r" facs="010">Fol. 10r</locus></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#32r" facs="032">Fol. 32r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1062CoronationMary">Coronation of Mary</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#60v" facs="061">Fol. 60v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1024MosesLaw">Moses Receiving Law</ref> with caption (l. to r.): <q>“His brother, Aaron,” “Holy Spirit,” “Prophet Moses with his tablet,” and “His singer sister, Miriam.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#81r" facs="081">Fol. 81r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1038Baptism">Baptism of Jesus</ref> with caption (l. to r.): <q>“River Jordan,” and “How John the Baptist baptized Our Lord Jesus Christ.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#101r" facs="101">Fol. 101r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion of Jesus</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#128v" facs="129">Fol. 128v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1049Resurrection">Resurrection of Jesus</ref> with caption (l. to r.):  <q>“Our Mother, Eve,” “How Our Lord Jesus Christ rose from the dead on the third day,” and “Our Father, Adam.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#129r" facs="129">Fol. 129r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1033Ascension">Ascension of Jesus</ref> with caption (top to bottom): <q>“Ascension of Our Lord Jesus Christ,” “Cherubim,” and “Seraphim.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d9">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#1r #28r #39v #47v #57r #69r #90r #103r #114r" facs="001 028 040 048 057 069 090 103 114">folss. 1r, 28r, 39v, 47v, 57r, 69r, 90r, 103r, 114r, </locus> (ornate haräg);
                      <locus target="#1r #12v" facs="001 013">1r, 12v, </locus> (alternating red and black dots);
                      <locus target="#6v #19r" facs="007 019">6v, 19r, </locus> (line of black dots);
                      <locus target="#68v" facs="069">68v</locus> (multiple full stops)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="e1">
                      <desc>
                        A small cross marks the midpoint of the psalms
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                        <desc>
                        words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#6v #18r #31v #44r #45r" facs="007 018 032 044 045">folss. 6v, 18r, 31v, 44r, 45r, </locus>, etc.);
                        and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#5r #10v #17v" facs="005 011 018">5r, 10v, 17v, </locus>);
                        erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#67v" facs="068">67v, </locus>);
                        text has been removed (<locus target="#20r #29v #37v" facs="020 030 038">20r, 29v, 37v</locus>, etc.)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                      <desc>
                        The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line.
                        Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an
                        appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line
                        (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line
                        (e.g., <locus target="#2r #2v #6r #10v" facs="002 003 006 011">fols. 2r, 2v, 6r, 10v</locus>).
                      </desc>
                    </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                    <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, 196 x 142 mm, four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards of the traditional wood, covered with tooled leather.</decoNote>
